# Stack Auth — components & configuration

## Built-in components

Available from `@stackframe/stack`:

```tsx
<SignIn />
<SignUp />
<UserButton />
<OAuthButtonGroup />
<CredentialSignIn />
<StackHandler />
```

**Requirement:** All Stack components require `StackProvider` + `StackTheme` in the React tree.

## Environment Variables

```bash
# Stack Auth (self-hosted)
NEXT_PUBLIC_STACK_PROJECT_ID=...
NEXT_PUBLIC_STACK_PUBLISHABLE_CLIENT_KEY=...  # (new docs: NEXT_PUBLIC_STACK_PUBLISHABLE_KEY)
STACK_SECRET_SERVER_KEY=...                   # (new docs: STACK_SECRET_KEY) NEVER in client code!
NEXT_PUBLIC_STACK_API_URL=http://localhost:8102

# Provider selection
AUTH_PROVIDER=stack
NEXT_PUBLIC_AUTH_PROVIDER=stack
```

The SDK supports both old and new env var names (backward-compatible).

## Cookie names (debugging)

Stack Auth SDK использует:
Stack Auth SDK uses:
- `stack-access` — access token (fixed name)
- `stack-refresh-{projectId}` — refresh token
- `stack-refresh` — legacy fallback

❌ Do NOT use `stack-refresh-token` or `stack-access-token` — those names do not exist in the SDK.

## Common pitfalls

❌ `new StackClientApp(...)` / `new StackServerApp(...)` — use `getStack*App()`  
❌ `useUser()` in a Server Component — use `getUser()` instead  
❌ `useUser()` outside `StackProvider` — runtime error  
❌ `<StackHandler {...props} />` — pass `routeProps={props}`  
❌ Removing `StackTheme` — built-in components break
